  <metadata>
    <id>empirica</id>
    <version>1.0.3</version>
    <title>Empirica - Epistemic Self-Assessment Framework</title>
    <authors>Empirica Team</authors>
    <owners>Empirica Team</owners>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/nubaeon/empirica/blob/main/LICENSE</licenseUrl>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/nubaeon/empirica</projectUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>
Empirica is an epistemic self-assessment framework for AI agents. It provides:

- CASCADE workflow (PREFLIGHT → Investigate → Plan → Act → CHECK → POSTFLIGHT)
- 13-vector epistemic state tracking
- Goal orchestration with dependency management
- Git-based session checkpoints and handoff reports
- MCP (Model Context Protocol) server integration
- Multi-provider AI adapter support (Claude, Gemini, GPT, Qwen, etc.)

Perfect for AI agents that need genuine metacognitive awareness and calibration.
    </description>
    <summary>Epistemic self-assessment framework for AI agents with CASCADE workflow</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
Release 1.0.3 (Patch):
- MCP moved to optional dependencies (core empirica no longer requires mcp package)
- Fixed duplicate mcp entry in optional dependencies
- Users who only need CLI don't have to install mcp
- Better package separation between empirica and empirica-mcp

Release 1.0.1 (Patch):
- Fixed SEMANTIC_INDEX.yaml v2.0 with correct documentation paths
- Moved Docker documentation to proper location (.docker/)
- Updated README with all installation methods
- Published empirica-mcp v1.0.0 to PyPI

Release 1.0.0 (Stable):
- MCO (Model-Centric Operations) system with persona support
- Complete CASCADE workflow (PREFLIGHT/CHECK/POSTFLIGHT)
- Unified storage via GitEnhancedReflexLogger
- Project bootstrap with uncertainty-driven context loading
- Session management with 97.5% token reduction
    </releaseNotes>
    <tags>ai llm epistemic metacognition self-assessment calibration python cli</tags>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="python" version="3.11.0" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
